cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "EduRobust: Multilingual Robustness Benchmark for Educational LLM Restrictions"
authors:
  - family-names: "Qiu"
    given-names: "Wei"
  - family-names: "Li"
    given-names: "Jiawei"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-03-18
url: "https://github.com/QWtail/EduRobust"
abstract: >
  EduRobust is a reproducible benchmarking framework that measures the multilingual
  robustness of educational behavioral restrictions in LLMs. It evaluates five
  forbidden behaviors across 24 languages, three open-source models, and 50 repeated
  trials per configuration — totaling 18,000 experiment cells — using a two-tier
  evaluation pipeline combining an LLM judge with keyword/language-detection fallbacks.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - multilingual safety
  - educational AI
  - prompt injection
  - robustness benchmark
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/QWtail/EduRobust"
